HEADWORD: Hydantoin
<hw>Hy*dan"to*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hyd</ets>rogen + all<ets>antion</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A derivative of urea, <chform>C3H4N2O2</chform>,
obtained from allantion, as a white, crystalline substance, with a
sweetish taste; -- called also <altname>glycolyl
urea</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

